+# Quarterly Learning Performance Summary (Synthetic)
+
+> Synthetic demonstration document. Figures are fabricated.
+
+## Headline metrics
+
+- Average study time across learners: 21 hours.
+- Overall pass rate: 68%.
+
+## Observations
+
+- Learners with more than 20 study hours **and** more than 75% on practice scores show markedly stronger certification outcomes.
+- Learners below 12 study hours rarely pass on the first attempt.
+- Practice score is a stronger predictor of outcome than raw hours once a minimum study threshold is met.
+
+## Recommendation
+
+Set a readiness gate: do not recommend booking the exam until a learner reaches both the 75% practice-score threshold and roughly 90% of the certification's recommended hours.
